bug.short_desc: Kernel 4.5.0 locks up on HP laptop

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: System locks up in one of two places (shortly after kvm start or disable due to bios and just as gdm is showing the mouse cursor but nothing else). I believe this is kernel because 4.3.x and 4.4.x from Fedora 23 do not show this even after upgrade to Fedora 24. 4.5.0 rc3 and final both show it.
This is on an HP laptop. I will provide more information on the laptop when I am near enough to get the model number and if I can get it to boot so I can get lspci, etc.
Actual model code: A6Y51UA#ABA Hewlett-Packard HP Pavilion dv6 Notebook PC/1805, BIOS F.13 11/29/2011

This is still a problem with 4.5.2-302 and mesa-dri-drivers-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-filesystem-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libEGL-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libgbm-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libGL-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libglapi-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libGLES-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libGLU-9.0.0-10.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libwayland-egl-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64 mesa-libxatracker-11.2.1-1.20160501.fc24.x86_64
The only error I have been able to see/find is in the attached image.
This appears to have been fixed in 4.5.4 (maybe the double-free issue mentioned for amdgpus). I will wait a few days before confirming this is fixed.
